41 // __cpp_exceptions is referred from
42 // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/manual/using_exceptions.html
43 // gcc < 5 does not define __cpp_exceptions but __EXCEPTIONS,
44 // Microsoft C++ Compiler does not provide an option to disable exceptions
45 #ifndef DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
46 #if __cpp_exceptions || __EXCEPTIONS \
47  || (defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__))
48 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 1
49 #else
50 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 0
51 #endif
52 #endif
53 
54 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
55 #define DNNL_TRAP() __builtin_trap()
56 #elif defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
57 #define DNNL_TRAP() __debugbreak()
58 #else
59 #error "unknown compiler"
60 #endif
61 
62 #if DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
63 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) throw error(status, msg)
64 #else
65 #include <cstdio>
66 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) \
67  do { \
68  fputs(msg, stderr); \
69  DNNL_TRAP(); \
70  } while (0)
71 #endif

87 struct error : public std::exception {
88  dnnl_status_t status;
89  const char *message;
90 
95  error(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message)
96  : status(status), message(message) {}
97 
99  const char *what() const noexcept override { return message; }
100 
106  static void wrap_c_api(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message) {
107  if (status != dnnl_success) DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, message);
108  }
109 };
110 
112 template <typename T>
113 struct handle_traits {};
114 
128 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
129 struct handle {
130 private:
131  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
132  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> data_ {0};
133 
134 protected:
135  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == data_.get(); }
136  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
137 
138 public:
146  handle() = default;
147 
149  handle(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
151  handle<T, traits> &operator=(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
153  handle(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
155  handle<T, traits> &operator=(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
156 
162  explicit handle(T t, bool weak = false) { reset(t, weak); }
163 
169  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
170  data_.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
171  }
172 
178  T get(bool allow_empty = false) const {
179  T result = data_.get();
180  if (allow_empty == false && result == nullptr)
181  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(
182  dnnl_invalid_arguments, "object is not initialized");
183  return result;
184  }
185 
190  explicit operator T() const { return get(true); }
191 
195  explicit operator bool() const { return get(true) != nullptr; }
196 
203  bool operator==(const handle<T, traits> &other) const {
204  return other.data_.get() == data_.get();
205  }
206 
213  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
214 };

360 dnnl::primitive::kind primitive::get_kind() const {
361  const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = get_primitive_desc();
362  // TODO (Roma): the code below is only needed because get_primitive_desc
363  // returns a C type.
364  dnnl_primitive_kind_t kind;
365  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
366  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&kind),
367  "could not get a primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
368  return static_cast<dnnl::primitive::kind>(kind);
369 }

631 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
632  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
633  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
634  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
635  } \
636 \
637  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
638  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
639  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
640  } \
641 \
642  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
643  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
644  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
645  } \
646 \
647  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
648  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
649  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
650  return lhs; \
651  } \
652 \
653  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
654  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
655  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
656  return lhs; \
657  } \
658 \
659  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
660  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
661  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
662  return lhs; \
663  } \
664 \
665  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
666  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
667  }
668 
669 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(normalization_flags)
670 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(rnn_flags)

982  void get_output_scales(int &mask, std::vector<float> &scales) const {
983  dnnl_dim_t count;
984  int c_mask;
985  const float *c_scales;
986  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_get_output_scales(
987  get(), &count, &c_mask, &c_scales),
988  "could not get primitive output scales attribute");
989  scales.resize(count);
990 
991  mask = c_mask;
992  for (dnnl_dim_t c = 0; c < count; ++c)
993  scales[c] = c_scales[c];
994  }

1148  const post_ops get_post_ops() const {
1149  post_ops result;
1150  const_dnnl_post_ops_t c_result;
1151  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_get_post_ops(get(), &c_result),
1152  "could not get primitive post-ops attribute");
1153  result.reset(const_cast<dnnl_post_ops_t>(c_result), true);
1154  return result;
1155  }
1156 
1165  void set_post_ops(const post_ops ops) {
1166  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_set_post_ops(get(), ops.get()),
1167  "could not set primitive post-ops attribute");
1168  }
1169 
1203  void set_rnn_data_qparams(float scale, float shift) {
1204  error::wrap_c_api(
1205  dnnl_primitive_attr_set_rnn_data_qparams(get(), scale, shift),
1206  "could not get primitive RNN data quantization parameters "
1207  "attributes");
1208  }
1209

1238  get(), (int)scales.size(), mask, &scales[0]),

1240  "attributes");
1241  }

1260 template <>
1261 struct handle_traits<dnnl_engine_t> {
1262  static constexpr auto destructor = &dnnl_engine_destroy;
1263 };
1265 
1267 struct engine : public handle<dnnl_engine_t> {
1268  friend struct primitive;
1269  friend struct reorder;
1270 
1272  enum class kind {
1274  any = dnnl_any_engine,
1276  cpu = dnnl_cpu,
1278  gpu = dnnl_gpu,
1279  };
1280 
1281  using handle::handle;
1282 
1285  engine() = default;
1286 
1291  static size_t get_count(kind kind) {
1292  return dnnl_engine_get_count(convert_to_c(kind));
1293  }
1294 
1300  engine(kind kind, size_t index) {
1301  dnnl_engine_t engine;
1302  error::wrap_c_api(
1303  dnnl_engine_create(&engine, convert_to_c(kind), index),
1304  "could not create an engine");
1305  reset(engine);
1306  }
1307 
1308 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1309  engine(kind kind, cl_device_id device, cl_context context) {
1316  dnnl_engine_t engine;
1317  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_create_ocl(
1318  &engine, convert_to_c(kind), device, context),
1319  "could not create an engine");
1320  reset(engine);
1321  }
1322 #endif
1323 
1328  engine(const handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> &pd) {
1329  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
1330  error::wrap_c_api(
1331  dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
1332  dnnl::convert_to_c(dnnl::query::engine), 0, &c_engine),
1333  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
1334  reset(c_engine, true);
1335  }
1336 
1339  kind get_kind() const {
1340  dnnl_engine_kind_t kind;
1341  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_kind(get(), &kind),
1342  "could not get kind of an engine");
1343  return static_cast<engine::kind>(kind);
1344  }
1345 
1346 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1347  cl_context get_ocl_context() const {
1350  cl_context context = nullptr;
1351  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_context(get(), &context),
1352  "could not get an OpenCL context fron an engine");
1353  return context;
1354  }
1355 
1358  cl_device_id get_ocl_device() const {
1359  cl_device_id device = nullptr;
1360  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_device(get(), &device),
1361  "could not get an OpenCL device fron an engine");
1362  return device;
1363  }
1364 #endif
1365 
1371  template <class primitive_desc>
1372  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd) {
1373  return query(pd, dnnl::query::engine);
1374  }
1375 
1376 private:
1377  static dnnl_engine_kind_t convert_to_c(kind kind) {
1378  return static_cast<dnnl_engine_kind_t>(kind);
1379  }
1380 
1381  template <class primitive_desc>
1382  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd, dnnl::query what) {
1383  dnnl_engine_t c_engine;
1384  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
1385  dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &c_engine),
1386  "could not get an engine from a primitive_desc");
1387  return engine(c_engine, true);
1388  }
1389 };

1409 struct stream : public handle<dnnl_stream_t> {

1411 
1413  enum class flags : unsigned {

1418  in_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1420  out_of_order = dnnl_stream_out_of_order,
1422  default_flags = dnnl_stream_default_flags,
1423  };
1424 
1427  stream() = default;
1428 
1434  stream(const engine &engine, flags flags = flags::default_flags) {
1435  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1436  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create(&stream, engine.get(),
1437  static_cast<dnnl_stream_flags_t>(flags)),
1438  "could not create a stream");
1439  reset(stream);
1440  }
1441 
1442 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1443  stream(const engine &engine, cl_command_queue queue) {
1448  dnnl_stream_t stream;
1449  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_ocl(&stream, engine.get(), queue),
1450  "could not create a stream");
1451  reset(stream);
1452  }
1453 
1456  cl_command_queue get_ocl_command_queue() const {
1457  cl_command_queue queue = nullptr;
1458  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_get_ocl_command_queue(get(), &queue),
1459  "could not get an OpenCL command queue from a stream");
1460  return queue;
1461  }
1462 #endif
1463 
1466  stream &wait() {
1467  error::wrap_c_api(
1468  dnnl_stream_wait(get()), "could not wait on a stream");
1469  return *this;
1470  }
1471 };

2094  desc(const memory::dims &dims, data_type data_type,
2095  format_tag format_tag, bool allow_empty = false)
2096  : data() {
2097  validate_dims(dims);
2098  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data,
2099  (int)dims.size(), dims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &dims[0],
2100  convert_to_c(data_type), convert_to_c(format_tag));
2101  if (!allow_empty)
2102  error::wrap_c_api(status,
2103  "could not construct a memory descriptor using a "
2104  "format tag");
2105  }
2106 
2122  desc(const memory::dims &dims, data_type data_type,
2123  const memory::dims &strides, bool allow_empty = false)
2124  : data() {
2125  validate_dims(dims);
2126  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data,
2127  (int)dims.size(), dims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &dims[0],
2128  convert_to_c(data_type),
2129  strides.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &strides[0]);
2130  if (!allow_empty)
2131  error::wrap_c_api(status,
2132  "could not construct a memory descriptor using "
2133  "strides");
2134  }
2135 
2139  desc(const dnnl_memory_desc_t &data) : data(data) {}

2143  //
2152  desc submemory_desc(const memory::dims &dims,
2153  const memory::dims &offsets, bool allow_empty = false) const {
2154  dnnl_memory_desc_t sub_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();
2155  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_memory_desc_init_submemory(
2156  &sub_md, &data, &dims[0], &offsets[0]);
2157  if (!allow_empty)
2158  error::wrap_c_api(status, "could not construct a sub-memory");
2159  return desc(sub_md);
2160  }

2207  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md = dnnl_memory_desc_t();

2209  &out_md, &data, (int)dims.size(), &dims[0]);
2210  if (!allow_empty)
2211  error::wrap_c_api(
2212  status, "could not reshape a memory descriptor");
2213  return desc(out_md);
2214  }

2256  &out_md, &data, &permutation[0]);

2514  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
2515  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
2516  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
2517  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md,
2518  query::exec_arg_md};
2519  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
2520  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
2521  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2522  "memory descriptor query is invalid");
2523 
2524  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
2525  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
2526  return cdesc ? memory::desc(*cdesc) : memory::desc();
2527  }

2678  dnnl_primitive_desc_t new_pd;

2697  primitive_desc_base(
2698  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind)
2699  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind::undef) {}
2700 
2712  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
2713  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind)
2714  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, prop_kind, prop_kind) {}
2715 
2729  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
2730  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1,
2731  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2) {
2732  // It is OK to pass an empty primitive descriptor
2733  if (pd == nullptr) return;
2734 
2735  dnnl_status_t rc;
2736 
2737  dnnl_primitive_kind_t c_prim_kind = convert_to_c(prim_kind);
2738  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
2739  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
2740 
2741  // Check that primitive kind matches
2742  dnnl_primitive_kind_t pd_kind;
2743  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
2744  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_kind);
2745  error::wrap_c_api(
2746  rc, "could not get primitive kind from a primitive descriptor");
2747  if (pd_kind != c_prim_kind)
2748  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2749  "primitive descriptor operation kind mismatch");
2750 
2751  // Check that propagation kind matches
2752  dnnl_prop_kind_t pd_prop_kind;
2753  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
2754  pd, dnnl_query_prop_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_prop_kind);
2755 
2756  // Something went wrong
2757  if (rc != dnnl_success && rc != dnnl_unimplemented)
2758  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2759  "could not get propagation kind from the primitive "
2760  "descriptor");
2761 
2762  // Everything is fine
2763  if ((rc == dnnl_unimplemented && c_prop_kind1 == dnnl_prop_kind_undef)
2764  || (rc == dnnl_success
2765  && (pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
2766  || pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind2))) {
2767  reset_with_clone(pd);
2768  return;
2769  }
2770 
2771  // We could get the propagation kind but there is a mismatch
2772  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2773  "primitive descriptor propagation kind mismatch");
2774  }
2775 
2776 protected:
2777  using base = primitive_desc_base;
2778 };
2779

2792 struct reorder : public primitive {
2794  struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
2795  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
2796 
2798  primitive_desc() = default;
2799 
2815  primitive_desc(const engine &src_engine, const memory::desc &src_md,
2816  const engine &dst_engine, const memory::desc &dst_md,
2817  const primitive_attr &attr = primitive_attr()) {
2818  dnnl_primitive_desc_t result;
2819  error::wrap_c_api(
2820  dnnl_reorder_primitive_desc_create(&result, &src_md.data,
2821  src_engine.get(), &dst_md.data, dst_engine.get(),
2822  attr.get()),
2823  "could not create a primitive descriptor for a reorder "
2824  "primitive");
2825  reset(result);
2826  }
2827 
2835  primitive_desc(const memory &src, const memory &dst,
2836  const primitive_attr &attr = primitive_attr()) {
2837  dnnl_primitive_desc_t result;
2838  auto src_md = src.get_desc();
2839  auto dst_md = dst.get_desc();
2840  error::wrap_c_api(
2841  dnnl_reorder_primitive_desc_create(&result, &src_md.data,
2842  src.get_engine().get(), &dst_md.data,
2843  dst.get_engine().get(), attr.get()),
2844  "could not create a primitive descriptor for a reorder "
2845  "primitive");
2846  reset(result);
2847  }
2848 
2853  primitive_desc(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd)
2854  : primitive_desc_base(pd, dnnl::primitive::kind::reorder) {}
2855 
2858  engine get_src_engine() const {
2859  return engine::query(*this, dnnl::query::reorder_src_engine);
2860  }
2861 
2864  engine get_dst_engine() const {
2865  return engine::query(*this, dnnl::query::reorder_dst_engine);
2866  }
2867 
2869  memory::desc src_desc() const { return base::src_desc(0); }
2870 
2872  memory::desc dst_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(0); }
2873  };
2874 
2876  reorder() = default;
2877 
2880  reorder(const primitive_desc &pd) : primitive(pd.get()) {}
2881 
2889  reorder(const memory &src, const memory &dst,
2890  const primitive_attr &attr = primitive_attr())
2891  : primitive(primitive_desc(src, dst, attr).get()) {}
2892 
2893  using primitive::execute;
2894 
2901  void execute(stream stream, memory &src, memory &dst) const {
2902  primitive::execute(stream, {{DNNL_ARG_FROM, src}, {DNNL_ARG_TO, dst}});
2903  }
2904 };

2917 inline std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> convert_to_c(
2918  const std::vector<memory::desc> &mems) {
2919  std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> c_mems;
2920  c_mems.reserve(mems.size());
2921  for (const auto &s : mems)
2922  c_mems.push_back(s.data);
2923  return c_mems;
2924 }

2928 struct concat : public primitive {
2930  struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
2931  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
2932 
2934  primitive_desc() = default;
2935 
2955  primitive_desc(const memory::desc &dst, int concat_dimension,
2956  const std::vector<memory::desc> &srcs, const engine &engine,
2957  const primitive_attr &attr = primitive_attr()) {
2958  auto c_srcs = convert_to_c(srcs);
2959 
2960  dnnl_primitive_desc_t result;
2961  error::wrap_c_api(
2962  dnnl_concat_primitive_desc_create(&result, &dst.data,
2963  (int)c_srcs.size(), concat_dimension, &c_srcs[0],
2964  attr.get(), engine.get()),
2965  "could not create a primitive descriptor for a concat "
2966  "primitive");
2967  reset(result);
2968  }
2969 
2982  primitive_desc(int concat_dimension,
2983  const std::vector<memory::desc> &srcs, const engine &engine,
2984  const primitive_attr &attr = primitive_attr()) {
2985  auto c_api_srcs = convert_to_c(srcs);
2986 
2987  dnnl_primitive_desc_t result;
2988  error::wrap_c_api(
2989  dnnl_concat_primitive_desc_create(&result, nullptr,
2990  (int)c_api_srcs.size(), concat_dimension,
2991  &c_api_srcs[0], attr.get(), engine.get()),
2992  "could not create a primitive descriptor for a concat "
2993  "primitive");
2994  reset(result);
2995  }

3002  : primitive_desc_base(pd, dnnl::primitive::kind::concat) {}

3129 
3132 struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
3133  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
3134 
3135  primitive_desc() = default;
3136 
3159  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
3160  const engine &engine, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd,
3161  bool allow_empty = false)
3162  : allow_empty_(allow_empty) {
3163  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
3164  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
3165  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, engine.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
3166  if (!allow_empty)
3167  error::wrap_c_api(
3168  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
3169  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
3170  fetch_impl();
3171  }
3172 
3177  bool next_impl() {
3178  dnnl_status_t status
3179  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
3180  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
3181  error::wrap_c_api(
3182  status, "could not advance a primitive descriptor iterator");
3183  fetch_impl();
3184  return true;
3185  }
3186 
3187 private:
3188  bool allow_empty_ = false;
3189  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
3190  void fetch_impl() {
3191  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
3192  pd_iterator.get(allow_empty_));
3193  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr || allow_empty_ ? dnnl_success
3194  : dnnl_runtime_error,
3195  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from a primitive "
3196  "descriptor iterator");
3197  reset(pd);
3198  }
3199 };

6887  return base::diff_weights_desc(0);
6888  }
6889 
6891  memory::desc diff_dst_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(0); }
6892 
6894  memory::desc diff_bias_desc() const {
6895  return base::diff_weights_desc(1);
6896  }
6897  };
6898 
6900  inner_product_backward_weights() = default;
6901 
6905  inner_product_backward_weights(const primitive_desc &pd) : primitive(pd) {}
6906 };

6919 struct rnn_primitive_desc_base : public primitive_desc {
6920  using primitive_desc::primitive_desc;
6921 
6923  rnn_primitive_desc_base() = default;
6924 
6932  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind,
6933  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind)
6934  : rnn_primitive_desc_base(pd, prop_kind, prop_kind, cell_kind) {}
6935 
6938  memory::desc src_layer_desc() const { return base::src_desc(0); }
6939 
6944  memory::desc src_iter_desc() const { return base::src_desc(1); }
6945 
6948  memory::desc src_iter_c_desc() const { return base::src_desc(2); }
6949 
6952  memory::desc weights_layer_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(0); }
6953 
6956  memory::desc weights_iter_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(1); }
6957 
6962  memory::desc bias_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(2); }
6963 
6966  memory::desc dst_layer_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(0); }
6967 
6972  memory::desc dst_iter_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(1); }
6973 
6976  memory::desc dst_iter_c_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(2); }
6977 
6980  memory::desc diff_src_layer_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(0); }
6981 
6986  memory::desc diff_src_iter_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(1); }
6987 
6990  memory::desc diff_src_iter_c_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(2); }
6991 
6994  memory::desc diff_weights_layer_desc() const {
6995  return base::diff_weights_desc(0);
6996  }
6997 
7000  memory::desc diff_weights_iter_desc() const {
7001  return base::diff_weights_desc(1);
7002  }
7003 
7008  memory::desc diff_bias_desc() const { return base::diff_weights_desc(2); }
7009 
7012  memory::desc diff_dst_layer_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(0); }
7013 
7018  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(1); }
7019 
7022  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_c_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(2); }
7023 
7024 protected:
7025  using rnn_base = rnn_primitive_desc_base;
7026 
7027  // (Deliberately not using doxygen comments)
7028  //
7029  // Constructs an RNN primitive descriptor base from a C API primitive
7030  // descriptor while checking that it actually describes the expected
7031  // primitive by comparing propagation and primitive kinds. Caller can
7032  // pass two options propagation kinds. This is typically used to check
7033  // that propagation kind is inference or training forward propagation.
7034  //
7035  // @param pd C API primitive descriptor.
7036  // @param prop_kind1 Expected propagation kind.
7037  // @param prop_kind2 Expected propagation kind.
7038  // @param cell_kind Expected cell kind.
7039  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
7040  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2,
7041  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind) {
7042  dnnl_rnn_desc_t *rnn_d;
7043  dnnl_status_t rc;
7044  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd, dnnl_query_rnn_d, 0, &rnn_d);
7045  error::wrap_c_api(rc,
7046  "could not retrieve a descriptor from a primitive descriptor "
7047  "for an RNN primitive");
7048 
7049  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
7050  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
7051  dnnl_alg_kind_t c_cell_kind = convert_to_c(cell_kind);
7052 
7053  bool ok = rnn_d->primitive_kind == dnnl_rnn
7054  && (rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
7055  || rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind2)
7056  && rnn_d->cell_kind == c_cell_kind;
7057 
7058  if (!ok)
7059  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
7060  "mismatch between expected and provided descriptors for an "
7061  "RNN primitive");
7062 
7063  reset_with_clone(pd);
7064  }
7065 };

9343  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_backward_desc_init(&data,
9344  convert_to_c(algorithm), nullptr,
9345  &diff_src_desc.data, &diff_dst_desc.data),
9346  "could not create a resampling backward data descriptor");
9347  }
9348 
9364  desc(algorithm algorithm, std::vector<float> factors,
9365  const memory::desc &diff_src_desc,
9366  const memory::desc &diff_dst_desc) {
9367  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_resampling_backward_desc_init(&data,
9368  convert_to_c(algorithm), &factors[0],
9369  &diff_src_desc.data, &diff_dst_desc.data),
9370  "could not create a resampling backward data descriptor");
9371  }
9372  };

9567 inline primitive::primitive(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t c_pd) {
9568  dnnl_primitive_t result;
9569  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_create(&result, c_pd),
9570  "could not create a primitive");
9571  reset(result);
9572 }
9573 
9574 inline primitive::primitive(const primitive_desc &pd) : primitive(pd.get()) {}
9575 
9576 inline void primitive::execute(
9577  stream &stream, const std::unordered_map<int, memory> &args) const {
9578  std::vector<dnnl_exec_arg_t> c_args;
9579  c_args.reserve(args.size());
9580  for (const auto &a : args)
9581  c_args.push_back({a.first, a.second.get(true)});
9582 
9583  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_execute(get(), stream.get(),
9584  (int)c_args.size(), c_args.data()),
9585  "could not execute a primitive");
9586 }
